            <p>1325 Walnut St<lb/>
                &#123; 10th Elul 5644<lb/>
                31 Aug 1884<lb/>
                Reverend &#38; Dear Sir<lb/>
                At the request of my<lb/> cousins Iline&#91;&#63;&#93;&#44; Ellen and Emily&#44; I state that<lb/> on mature consideration they desire that the only<lb/> service at the House tomorrow for their lamented<lb/> Brother shall be confined to the recital of the<lb/> two psalms &#40;90<hi rend="sup">th</hi> &#38; 23<hi rend="sup">rd</hi>&#41; already selected&#44; in Hebrew<lb/> and English in the parlours on the first floor.<lb/>
                With their grateful appreciation and<lb/> thanks for your kind sympathy and thoughtfulness<lb/> and my respectful regard<lb/>
                I am truly yours<lb/>
                Isaac Phillips.<lb/>
                Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi> S. Morais.<lb/></p>
        </body>
